Add a robust configuration management system to the Forever library. Create `src/config.js` (replacing or extending the stub) with the following capabilities: 1) Load configuration from multiple sources in priority order: environment variables (ENV_*), a local `.foreverrc.json` file, and built-in defaults. 2) Support nested configuration keys using dot notation (e.g. `config.get('server.port')`). 3) Implement `config.set(key, value)` for runtime overrides. 4) Implement `config.validate(schema)` that checks all required keys are present and of the correct type, returning an array of validation errors. 5) Implement `config.watch(key, callback)` that calls `callback(newValue, oldValue)` whenever a key changes at runtime. 6) Implement `config.reset()` to restore factory defaults. 7) Implement `config.toJSON()` which returns a sanitized snapshot (masking any keys whose names contain 'password', 'secret', or 'token'). 8) Write tests in `tests/config.test.js` that verify all of the above behaviours. 9) Update `src/index.js` to export the new config module. 10) Add a `forever info config` example to `DOCUMENTATION.md`.